x; see eq. (5)) is the result of how prey fitness is impacted by changes in prey biomass (x), predator biomass (y), defense (u) and offense (v); the same holds true for the predator fitness (W
y). Using this principle, with the Geber method1 we decompose the temporal dynamics of W
